<item>
            <title>[LU-18864] Improve how lnet_selftest handles non primary nids</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18864</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;lnet_selftest cannot be used with nids that are not primary.&lt;br/&gt;
When it is used with non primary nids, there is nothing pointing to this problem in the logs or in kernel messages, only a timeout error.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There are two possibilities to improve that:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Print relevant message to explain primary nids have to be used.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Handle non primary nids.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
