                            <comment id="450344" author="adilger" created="Sat, 29 Mar 2025 05:40:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;My strong preference would be to allow using the non-primary NID transparently. If the code can detect this case and print an error message that tells the user to use the primary NID, it could just use the primary NID directly and just print a message that it is doing so (or not at all if LST is doing MR testing. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
